definition: to mention sth without elaborating (idiom); not giving details

sentences.english: The thirty-second day out of Bombay began inauspiciously.
sentences.chinese: 离开孟买的第三十二天就开始就出现了不详之兆。

sentences.english: Algiers Sundays are among the most sinister.
sentences.chinese: 阿尔及尔的礼拜日是最为不详。

sentences.english: An unknown number of personnels are still trapped under the debris.
sentences.chinese: 据信还有数目不详的人员被困在瓦砾下。

sentences.english: Punning in Chinese has a long history, though it is of uncertain origin.
sentences.chinese: 汉语双关名称来源不详，但其使用源远流长。

sentences.english: An unknown amount of the lending has flowed into the stock market.
sentences.chinese: 同时有一部分数额不详的贷款进入了股市。

sentences.english: Her status with respect to tuberculin skin testing was unknown.
sentences.chinese: 病人的结核菌素皮肤试验结果不详。

sentences.english: A woman hugs a tree in the gardens of Liberty Square in Taipei, date unknown.
sentences.chinese: 抱树的女子，摄于台北自由广场，日期不详。

sentences.english: Date of birth unknown, died Yuanshizhu Emperor Yuan 20 years.
sentences.chinese: 生年不详，卒于元世祖至元二十六年。

sentences.english: The date of birth and death of Qu Yuan is unknown.
He feared something was wrong, but didn't tell Marianne.
sentences.chinese: 他有种不详的预感，但没有告诉玛丽安。

sentences.english: As usual it gives few details of China’s own weapons.
sentences.chinese: 像往常一样，该文件对中国所持有的武器语焉不详。

sentences.english: The old gentleman, birth year is unknown.
The type of snakes released, including whether any were dangerous, had yet to be determined.
sentences.chinese: 投放的蛇种类不详，是否有害也情况不明。

sentences.english: North-West Frontier people, life of anonymity.
sentences.chinese: 西北边境人，生平姓名不详。

sentences.english: Six suicide bombers made it inside and an unknown number of gunmen.
sentences.chinese: 六名自杀式炸弹袭击者和人数不详的枪手潜入大楼里。

definition: dates of birth and death (of historical figure)
dates of birth and death (of historical figure)
one's native place/place of ancestry/registered birthplace
not to have access/beyond one's authority or capability/sth one has no way of doing
to do textual research/to make textual criticism/to verify by means of research (esp. historical details)/to take an exam to get a certificate (abbr. for 考取證件|考取证件[kao3 qu3 zheng4 jian4])
